				<OwnerUserId>192</OwnerUserId>
			</Contributors>
			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;In my experience, as well as accounts of others' experiences, it seems that clear and green bottles are inferior to brown bottles for storing beer. I know this is due to the amount of light allowed through the bottle.&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;But why do breweries continue to use green and (especially) clear bottles? Why bother with a bottle that is more likely to allow beer to spoil?&lt;/p&gt;

				</Text>
			</Body>
